        "answer_count": 3,
        "title": "Trouble bubble sorting (recursion) an array of integers in Java",
        "body": "<p>Attempting to implement a recursive method to sort an array of integers:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    public static void bubbleSort(int[] arr, int n){\n\n      int index = n-1;\n\n      System.out.println(\"Round number: \" + n);\n      System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));\n\n      while(index&gt;=1)\n      {\n          if(arr[index] &lt;  arr[index-1])\n              swap(arr, index, index-1);\n\n\n          index--;\n      }\n      if(n&gt;1)\n          bubbleSort(arr, n-1);\n  }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>}<\/p>\n\n<p>It seems to work fine for the first few rounds, moving the smallest integer in the set to the front, but it just stops working around midway. Any idea why? Thanks!<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 18070234,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "arrays",
            "sorting",
            "recursion"
        ],
        "score": 0,
